Date: Wed 9 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency online, Wed 9 Mar 2005 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-03/09/content_2674059.htm>

Viet Nam: another asymptomatic case of avian influenza H5N1 virus infection
-----------------------------------------------
A 68-year-old widow from Viet Nam's northern Thai Binh province, wife of an
avian influenza patient, has just been confirmed to have contracted avian
influenza virus H5N1, raising the total [number of infections in the
country since late December 2004] to 24, a local health official told
Xinhua on Wed 9 Mar 2005.
"According to testing by the National Hygiene and Epidemiology Institute
today [Wed 9 Mar 2005], specimens from the woman from Kien Xuong district
tested positive for H5N1 virus. She had slaughtered a chicken for a meal on
the 3rd day of the Lunar New Year Festival (early February 2005)," said
Pham Gia Lai, deputy director of the Thai Binh Health Department. The
woman, who is now in good health in her home town, will receive treatment
with the anti-viral drug Tamiflu, he said.
The woman's 69-year-old husband developed symptoms of avian influenza on 19
Feb 2005, was admitted to the Thai Binh Hospital on the same day, and died
on 23 Feb 2005. Testing by the institute in the capital city of Hanoi
indicated that he was a bird flu victim.
